# GoodContent — Architecture

## Product Overview

GoodContent is a HubSpot-native SaaS app that replaces human content writers with an AI interviewer. Marketing teams create content briefs, share a guest link to a subject matter expert or customer, and the AI conducts an async voice interview. The transcript is synthesised into a polished draft and pushed directly to HubSpot.

Every piece of content progresses through seven codified phases: **Brief → Research → Outline → Interview → Draft → Edit → Review**. See `product.mdc` for phase semantics.

---

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | Next.js 16 (App Router, TypeScript) |
| Database | Convex (real-time, serverless, TypeScript-native) |
| Auth | Clerk (HubSpot OAuth for workspace login, JWT guest tokens for interview links) |
| Voice Synthesis (TTS) | ElevenLabs — Flash v2.5 model (~75ms latency, 32+ languages) |
| Speech-to-Text (STT) | Deepgram Nova-3 — WebSocket streaming, real-time transcription |
| AI / LLM | Anthropic Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-20250514) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui |
| Billing | Polar.sh (credit-based subscriptions) |
| File Storage | Cloudflare R2 (audio recordings, exported documents) |
| HubSpot Integration | HubSpot API v3 — CMS, Blog, Marketing |
| Error Monitoring | Sentry |
| Email | Resend |

