## Key Flows

### 1. Brief Creation (Phase: Brief)
1. User picks `contentType` → `briefTemplates.ts` supplies defaults
2. User edits title, topic, keywords, tone, formatting rules
3. User picks `interviewerLanguage` and `outputLanguage` (may differ)
4. User marks brief `ready` → `phase` transitions to `research`

### 2. Research (Phase: Research)
1. Claude reviews `sources[]`, runs keyword/SERP research, generates research notes
2. Notes stored in `research` table, rendered for user review
3. User edits or approves → `phase` transitions to `outline`
4. Credits deducted: `CREDIT_COST_RESEARCH`

### 3. Outline (Phase: Outline)
1. Claude proposes H2/H3 outline from brief + approved research
2. User edits and approves → `phase` transitions to `interview`
3. Interview questions finalised at this step using approved outline

### 4. Interview Link Generation & Guest Room (Phase: Interview)
1. System generates a cryptographically random guest token (UUID), stores hash in `interviews.guestTokenHash`
2. Raw token returned once to user to share via `https://goodcontent.ai/interview/[token]`
3. Guest opens link, sees consent screen, consents → recording begins
4. Deepgram WebSocket opens for real-time STT in `interviewerLanguage`
5. ElevenLabs Flash v2.5 voices questions in `interviewerLanguage`
6. Claude monitors transcript, injects dynamic follow-ups (max 3 per question)
7. Audio streamed to Cloudflare R2; transcript stored in Convex on completion
8. `phase` transitions to `draft`
9. Credits deducted per minute: `CREDIT_COST_INTERVIEW_PER_MINUTE`

### 5. Draft Generation (Phase: Draft)
1. Transcript + brief + research + approved outline + formatting rules sent to Claude
2. Claude generates full draft in `outputLanguage`
3. Draft built with SEO (meta, slug, schema) and AEO (FAQ, structured answers) features
4. Internal link suggestions generated against already-pushed drafts in the workspace
5. Draft stored; `phase` transitions to `edit`
6. Credits deducted: `CREDIT_COST_GENERATION`

### 6. Edit (Phase: Edit)
1. User edits inline, regenerates sections as needed, toggles SEO/AEO features
2. User marks draft `edited` → `phase` transitions to `review`
3. No credits consumed for editing; section regeneration consumes per-generation credit

### 7. Review (Phase: Review)
1. Admin or creator reviews final draft
2. If `workspace.autoApproveReview === true` and reviewer is creator, auto-approved
3. On approval → `phase` transitions to `pushed` and HubSpot push is enabled

### 8. HubSpot Push
1. User selects draft(s) and clicks "Push to HubSpot"
2. App maps content type to HubSpot API endpoint
3. Internal link suggestions resolved to HubSpot URLs (if target already pushed)
4. HubSpot API v3 call creates/updates content
5. Supports bulk upload for multiple approved drafts at once

